The Copenhagen Wheel provides users battery assisted rides and collects data along its use - <em>capturing congestion, air pollution, trip data, etc</em> . How much more would it cost to outfit a bike share program with sensor laden hubs? Do the long term benefits to civil services outweight the origin.

&nbsp;

The Bike Share app would have to run some CPHWheel build in order for city/public to access the data.

In addition to being a city planning data scientist's dream, I'd love to get these two

Milwaukee wants to bring more city bikes to the city, <a title="Fox News Report" href="%20http://fox6now.com/2013/12/05/committee-okays-expansion-of-bike-sharing-program/">28 more stations</a> to be exact.

&nbsp;

If Trek's CEO wants to make Milwaukee and Madison more bike friendly, what better start than blanketing the data in biking data.

